# =============================================================================
# INSTRUCTIONS FOR IMPLEMENTATION
# =============================================================================

# To implement soft ownership in your repository:
#
# 1. Choose your implementation method:
#    a) GitHub Apps/Actions that read this file and add optional reviewers
#    b) Manually reference during PR reviews
#    c) Convert to regular CODEOWNERS during important releases
#
# 2. Create automation (example GitHub Action):
#    - Parse CODEOWNERS-soft on PR creation
#    - Add teams/users as optional reviewers
#    - Post comment explaining soft ownership
#
# 3. Customize team notifications:
#    - Use different notification levels (Slack, email, etc.)
#    - Create dashboard showing soft ownership coverage
#    - Integrate with your existing review processes
#
# 4. Regular maintenance:
#    - Review soft ownership patterns quarterly
#    - Update based on team feedback and collaboration needs
#    - Monitor for patterns that should become hard ownership
#
# 5. Team training:
#    - Educate teams on when to check soft ownership
#    - Establish guidelines for cross-team collaboration
#    - Create processes for escalating soft-owned changes

# =============================================================================
# NOTIFICATION PREFERENCES (OPTIONAL)
# =============================================================================

# You can extend this concept to include notification preferences:
# Format: path @team:notification-level
# Where notification-level could be: mention, watch, ignore
#
# Examples:
# /shared/ @frontend-team:mention @backend-team:watch
# /config/ @devops-team:mention @all-teams:watch
#
# This would require custom tooling to implement.
